# Swimlane Journal — Windsurf Rules

## Project overview

Single-file HTML/CSS/JS app (`Swimlane_App.html`). No build step, no npm, no server.
All JavaScript is one IIFE inside a `<script>` tag. State is in IndexedDB.
See CLAUDE.md for full architecture notes.

## Testing workflow — do this before every commit

**Before committing any change to `Swimlane_App.html`:**

1. Quick syntax check (instant, no browser):
```powershell
$html = Get-Content Swimlane_App.html -Raw -Encoding UTF8
$js = $html.Substring($html.IndexOf('<script>') + 8, $html.LastIndexOf('</script>') - $html.IndexOf('<script>') - 8)
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText("extracted.js", $js, [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8)
node --check extracted.js; Remove-Item extracted.js
```

2. Full smoke suite (7 automated browser tests):
```
node tests/smoke.js
```

Exit 0 = all pass. Exit 1 = see output for which test failed and why.
Screenshots saved to `tests/screenshots/` for visual verification.

The git pre-commit hook (`tools/pre-commit`, installed via `tools/install-hooks.ps1`)
runs `node tests/smoke.js` automatically on every commit and blocks if any test fails.
Do not use `--no-verify` unless the failure is a known fluke and you can explain why.

## When to run the browser-check tool

Run `node tools/browser-check.js` whenever:
- A white screen or blank page is reported
- JavaScript appears to render as plain text in the browser
- Any change is made to the `<script>` block in `Swimlane_App.html`
- A "SyntaxError" or "Invalid or unexpected token" is suspected

The tool launches a headless Chromium browser via Playwright, loads the file,
captures all page-level JS errors and console warnings, checks that the DOM has
rendered content, and saves a screenshot to `tools/screenshot.png`.

## How to run it

```
node tools/browser-check.js
```

Or for a specific file:

```
node tools/browser-check.js path/to/file.html
```

Exit code 0 = pass (no JS errors, day blocks rendered).
Exit code 1 = fail (see output for details).

## Common errors and what they mean

| Error message | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `Invalid or unexpected token` | Broken string literal or illegal character in JS | Check the `escape` function, look for `'\\'` followed by orphan `'` |
| `Uncaught SyntaxError: Unexpected end of input` | Unbalanced braces/brackets | Check for missing `}` or `)` in the IIFE |
| White screen, no page errors | DOM not built — check `VirtualScroll.init()` | Look for runtime errors in `bootstrap()` |
| JS renders as text | `</script>` literal inside a `<script>` comment | Escape it as `<\/script>` |
| `browserType.launch: Executable doesn't exist` | Chromium not installed | Run `npx playwright install chromium` |

## HTML-in-script pitfalls (hard-won lessons)

1. **Never put `</script>` literally inside a `<script>` block** — even in a comment.
   The HTML parser terminates the script tag there. Use `<\/script>` instead.

2. **Single-quote strings in JS that contain `'`** — use a double-quoted string to
   avoid escaping headaches: `"&#39;"` not `'\''`.

3. **HTML entities in `<script>` tags are NOT decoded** — `&amp;` stays as the
   literal string `&amp;` in JavaScript. This is correct for the `Utils.escape`
   function whose output should be HTML entity strings.

## JavaScript syntax check (no browser needed)

To quickly check JS syntax without launching a browser:

```powershell
$html = Get-Content Swimlane_App.html -Raw -Encoding UTF8
$start = $html.IndexOf('<script>') + '<script>'.Length
$end   = $html.LastIndexOf('</script>')
$js    = $html.Substring($start, $end - $start)
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText("extracted.js", $js, [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8)
node --check extracted.js
Remove-Item extracted.js
```

